Posing is definitely an Art.🧘🏾‍♀️ I’ve always been the kind of girl that takes every day as it comes. So many girls second-think their pose or what they’re doing.- @cocorocha  I’ve been blessed to have been able to be trusted to show my range and turn into a chameleon as so I’ve been told over the years with being able to make my mark in a diverse array of modeling forms. In this I have just been free to turn into whatever the client is looking for. Posing in front of the camera and being able to be anything is my favorite part of what I do. Don’t second guess yourself. You can do anything you put your mind to. Don’t fit into a box even if someone tells you that’s where you fit. Crush that box with your whole heart, mind, and spirit!  #followyourdreams#followyourheart #explorepage#pose#poses#posesforpictures #outofthebox #havefun#explore#officialchasteen

Throw back to @therubyball sponsored by sickle cell advocate Ijeoma Azubuko. This event raised $10,000 for @scdaa educational and awareness efforts. At this event I had the honor of speaking my truths with Sickle Cell Disease. This was my first in depth speech on the issue and will not be my last. It was truly gratifying and I cannot wait to continue on my path of inspiring and increasing awareness on this condition.  Since then I began @loveflawsfoundation to empower and unite individuals with scars invisible and visible through fashion and art to foster a transformative shift in the societal lens of beauty and strength.

Thank you to all involved!

A message from our CEO @officialchasteen  Picture imperfect photoshoot and makeover opportunity! Link in bio for registration! Do you or anyone you know have a Scar? Wether it be a birthmark, a traumatic event, or even an emotional trauma that you have experienced. We want to hear your story. We will be selecting candidates for this free photoshoot and makeover where you will:
-Have your hair, makeup, and styling done by top professionals in the fashion and beauty industry.
- Be guided by CEO and super model Bethany Chasteen infront of the camera.
-We will shoot some video content to capture the experience.

Individuals selected will experience a fashion experience of a lifetime, receive the final images of themselves to keep, and will be highlighted on our social media platforms. Later you will have a VIP invite to our future events.

Let us bring awareness, uplift and show the power and beauty of being uniquely you!

Fearlessly Loving Anyone With Scars!

Criteria to apply!
1: Follow us on Instagram 
2: Live or be able to comute to the Nyc area and be available for the full day of September 23, 2023
3: Must over 18 or over.
You have up to August 23 to submit. We look forward to seeing you soon!

For any questions and/or inquiries to be a volunteer to help in our photoshoot and mission email us at info@loveflaws.org

Join the Flawclub!

We would love your support in our mission. Participate in executing our Picture Imperfect Makeover Campaigns as photographers, designers, Makeup artists, Hair stylists, Brand Partnerships, and volunteers. The glitz, the glam, the auditions, the shoots, how does supermodel and sickle cell warrior, Bethany Chasteen, juggle it all?

In this video, supermodel, nurse, and activist, Bethany (@officialchasteen) shares a typical week in her life.

Want to know more about sickle cell and its impact on celebrities? Join today’s episode of #CandidConversations at 3:30 PM (PT).

Join Hollywood Film Director and sickle cell caregiver, Meko Winbush (@MekoWinbush), Actor and Warrior, Ramon Reed (@IAmRamon.Reed) and of course Supermodel - Bethany Chasteen discuss the importance of using their notoriety/celebrity to raise awareness for sickle cell disease. 

We look forward to having you join us.
